    dc:description "Fig. 5. A. Pleuroseta occidentalis sp. nov. paratype, left wing, ventral view (debu00244165). B. Pleuroseta occidentalis paratype, hypandrium, dorsal view (debu00245797). C. Pleuroseta wentworthi (Richards, 1973), hypandrium, dorsal view (debu00264733). D. Pleuroseta ingens sp. nov. paratype, hypandrium, dorsal view (debu00160984). E. Pleuroseta monteithi sp. nov. paratype, hypandrium, dorsal view (debu00160892). Scale bars: A=0.50 mm, B–E=0.10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10306508/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10306524>
    dc:description "Fig. 12. Pleuroseta wentworthi (Richards, 1973).A. Male habitus, lateral view (debu00403539).B. Male terminalia, lateral view (debu00264733). C. Male terminalia, posterolateral view (debu00264733). Abbreviations: epa =epandrium; hyp=hypandrium; se = subepandrial sclerite; ss =surstylus. Scale bars: A =1.0 mm; B–C =0.30 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10306524/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10306526>
    dc:description "Fig. 13. Pleuroseta wentworthi (Richards, 1973) (debu00264733). A. Aedeagus and associated structures, lateral view. B. Male S5–8, ventral view. Abbreviations: bp = basiphallus; dp =distiphallus; ea= ejaculatory apodeme; pg =postgonite; phal=phallapodeme. Scale bars: A–B =0.30 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10306526/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10306528>
    dc:description "Fig. 14. Pleuroseta wentworthi (Richards, 1973) (debu00264635). A. Female terminalia, dorsal view. B. Female terminalia, ventral view. C. Spermathecae. Abbreviations: cer =cercus; epi =epiproct; hyp =hypoproct. Scale bars: A–B = 0.40 mm; C = 0.06 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10306528/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10306530>
    dc:description "Fig. 15. A. Pleuroseta wentworthi (Richards, 1973) holotype, ♂, habitus, lateral view. B. Pleuroseta dorrigonis (Richards, 1973) holotype, ♂, habitus, lateral view. Scale bar: A–B =1.0 mm. Photo credit: N. Tees and R. Cox (AMSA)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10306530/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10306534>
    dc:description "Fig. 16. Pleuroseta left wings, ventral view. A. Pleuroseta ingens sp. nov. paratype (debu00162128). B. Pleuroseta monteithi sp. nov. paratype (debu00160892). C. Pleuroseta wentworthi (Richards, 1973) (debu402972). Scale bar: A–C= 0.5 mm." ;
